# Java / Spring Conventions

## Package Structure (per module)

```
com.aiconomy.{module}/
  config/       # @Configuration, beans
  domain/       # JPA entities (internal only)
  dto/          # Request/response records
  event/        # Kafka listeners/producers (or use common events)
  repository/   # Spring Data interfaces
  service/      # Business logic
  web/          # @RestController (thin)
```

## Rules

- Controllers: validate input (`@Valid`), delegate to service, return DTOs — no `@Transactional` in controllers.
- Services: `@Transactional` boundaries; throw domain exceptions, not generic `RuntimeException`.
- Entities: never expose directly via REST; map to DTOs.
- Concurrency on accounts: `@Version` optimistic lock; `PESSIMISTIC_WRITE` only when documented.
- Kafka consumers: idempotent processing with event ID deduplication table or Redis set.
- Configuration: `@ConfigurationProperties` + env vars; never hardcode secrets.

## Example — thin controller

```java
@PostMapping("/transfers")
public TransferResponse transfer(@Valid @RequestBody TransferRequest request) {
    return transferService.execute(request);
}
```

Business rules belong in `TransferService`, not here.
